                        h3 O prezentacji:
                        p Hibernate was started in 2001 as an alternative to using EJB2-style entity beans. But today EJB is forgotten and everybody wants to make modern software with Java 8 features. Hibernate is de facto industry standard. But what if it isn’t universal solution for all systems? How to do better declarative or functional querying?
                        p Let’s put aside classic Object-Relational Mapping and look at other, modern capabilities to know pros and cons of DSLs, lambdas and streams usage with relational databases.
                        p Theory, slides, comparisons, but also practical tips and many code examples in IDE.
